<DIV CLASS="c5"><BR><BR><P CLASS="c37"><SPAN CLASS="c31">n46&nbsp; Bruce Cadwallader, </SPAN><SPAN CLASS="c38">Two Officers Disciplined,</SPAN><SPAN CLASS="c31"> COLUMBUS DISPATCH, Apr. 30, 1992, at A1. Waugh, an African American and former varsity wrestler at Ohio State University, was struck in the head twice and sprayed repeatedly with mace simply for walking in the street to avoid a fight that was taking place on the sidewalk. Similar to the King case, the officers in Waugh's case were found not guilty in their trial for the criminal use of excessive force.</SPAN></P>
